Date: 07 April 2017 By: Isabel VenterViewed: 2097Police in Louis Trichardt are on the look-out for five suspects who shot and injured a guest staying over at the Lalapanzi Hotel on the N1 south. &nbsp;According to local police spokesperson Const Irene Radzilane, five armed suspects managed to gain entry into one of the guest units at the hotel. The robbers then shot and injured a male guest in his left thigh before fleeing with his laptop and cellphone.It is alleged that the suspects cut through the wire fence of the hotel to gain entry. The incident was reported at 03:45.Police are calling on the public to assist them with any information that might lead to an arrest. The Makhado Police station can be contacted at Tel 015&nbsp;519 4300 or 079 889 6222. Alternatively, the Crime Stop number can be called at 0860 01 0111 or the 24-hour crime line at 32211.&nbsp;Isabel joined the Zoutpansberger and Limpopo Mirror in 2009 as a reporter. She holds a BA Degree in Communication Sciences from the University of South Africa. Her beat is mainly crime and court reporting.Email: isabel@zoutnet.co.zaMore photos... 